      "message": "I went off of https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/297178/how-usb-bus-number-and-device-number-been-assigned \n```\nDevice numbers are simply counters: the first device connected gets a 1, the next gets a 2, and so on. But there is a little more: USB was designed to be hot-pluggable; \n```\n\nFrom reading through https://superuser.com/questions/1711806/the-naming-convention-of-folders-in-sys-bus-usb-devices it looks like the port#0 is reserved for the hub itself which get the .0. and the downstream ports get numbered from 1.",
